Sentencas: Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) cathodes operating in ambient atmospheric conditions inevitably encounter CO2 contamination, leading to sustained performance deterioration.
Titulo: Mechanistic Study on the Corrosion of (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Cathodes Induced by CO2

Sentencas: In this investigation, we examined the impact of CO2 on three variants of (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-delta cathodes and employed the distribution of relaxation times method to distinguish distinct electrochemical processes based on impedance spectra analysis.
Titulo: Mechanistic Study on the Corrosion of (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Cathodes Induced by CO2

Sentencas: We meticulously analyzed and discussed the corrosion resistance of these (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-delta cathodes under high CO2 concentrations, relying on the experimental data.
Titulo: Mechanistic Study on the Corrosion of (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Cathodes Induced by CO2

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy results revealed that La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF-6428), La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF-4628), and La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta (LSCFN-46271) cathodes exhibited persistent degradation when exposed to CO2 at temperatures of 650 degrees C or 800 degrees C during the durability-testing period.
Titulo: Mechanistic Study on the Corrosion of (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Cathodes Induced by CO2

Sentencas: An increase in electrode polarization resistance was observed upon CO2 introduction to the electrode, but electrode performance recovered upon returning to a pure air environment.
Titulo: Mechanistic Study on the Corrosion of (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Cathodes Induced by CO2

Sentencas: Furthermore, X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy analyses confirmed that CO2 did not cause permanent damage to the (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-delta cathodes.
Titulo: Mechanistic Study on the Corrosion of (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Cathodes Induced by CO2

Sentencas: These findings indicate that the (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-delta cathodes exhibit excellent resistance to CO2-induced corrosion.
Titulo: Mechanistic Study on the Corrosion of (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Cathodes Induced by CO2
